# =============================================================================
# geometry/2D_sediment_grain_test.opts — SMOKE TEST for igakit-generated
# non-rectangular geometry (rectangle with a semicircular sediment-grain
# "bite" cut from the bottom edge).
#
# Generated by preprocess/build_geometry_sediment_grain.py:
#   Lx = Ly = 4.0e-5 m, R_sed = 1.0e-5 m, 80x80 elements.
# -geom_file overrides -p/-C/-Nx/-Ny axis setup with the geometry's own
# (degree (1,1), C0 -- smooth-bump bottom edge, ruled to a flat top edge).
#
# IC reuses two_ice_grains_boundary (placed by index ratio in [0,Lx]x[0,Ly],
# NOT physical coordinates from the geometry map -- a mechanics-only smoke
# test, not a physically meaningful sediment-grain setup). Non-rectangular
# domain cannot be periodic -> -periodic 0, natural (zero-flux) BCs.
# =============================================================================
-geom_file inputs/geometry/sediment_grain_test.dat
-ic_type two_ice_grains_boundary
-dim 2
-Lx 4.0e-5
-Ly 4.0e-5
-Lz 0
-RCice0 9.375e-6
-RCice1 1.875e-5
-delt_t 1.0e-8
-eps 4.6648e-07
-periodic 0
